The paper proposes a reinforcement learning hyper-heuristic scheme for multi-objective optimization problems. This involves the use of domination amount, crowding distance, and hypervolume calculations to meet various optimization requirements adaptively and autonomously. The paper also applies the proposed approach to a generic structural fault identification problem. Based on this, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning), as the paper involves the use of reinforcement learning and heuristics. The next likely sub-categories are cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control), as the paper deals with optimization problems. Finally, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also a possible sub-category, as the paper discusses the development of a software tool for multi-objective optimization.
